---> nvm command not working in neovim terminal emulator.
  The reason for this is given in file ./observations-during-shell-configuration.
  Read it and fix the issue.

---> command not found after yarn global install `yarn global add yalc`. Why?
A. [Refer: https://stackoverflow.com/a/40333409/11320006]
  You should add export PATH="$PATH:$(yarn global bin)" to your ~/.bash_profile 
  or whatever you use. It would solve the issue.

  Depending on how you installed it, Yarn's global folder varies for some reason.
  You can follow this issue here.
